The paper deals with the construction of perfect hash functions and their applications in graph algorithms. This falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of color-coding technique suggests that the paper may also belong to the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The construction of hash functions involves geometric considerations, which may place the paper in the category of computational geometry (cs.CG). Finally, the use of approximation algorithms suggests that the paper may also belong to the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
